==English==

===Pronunciation===
pûr'spĭkā'shəs

===Adjective===
#Having the power of seeing or understanding clearly; quick-sighted; sharp of sight.
#(''[[figurative]]'') Of acute [[discernment]]; [[keen]]; mentally perceptive.

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1548|1548]], from [[Late Latin]] '''[[perspicacitas]]''' literally meaning "discernment", from [[Latin]] '''[[perspicax]]''' literally meaning "sharp-sighted", from '''[[perspicere]]''' meaning "to look through", from '''[[per-]]''' "through" + '''[[specere]]''' "look at". See also [[perspective]].

